28/07/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul says Turkey remains undecided about joining a future international peacekeeping force in Lebanon.
Speaking late Wednesday (26 July) upon his return from the Middle East summit in Rome, Gul said the international force must be backed by a UN resolution, with a ceasefire declared first.
In other news, a Turkish military airplane F-5A crashed seconds after take-off Thursday in central Turkey.
The pilot and the two soldiers aboard were killed.
(Turkishpress.com - 27/07/06)
